body: CMakeLists.txt (cmake) now support release and debug builds. Extend AddCompilerFlag.cmake about functions that allow easily to add compile flags for different build types. These build types are integrated in the CMakeLists.txt file. This make cmake builds more straight forward. `cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release` optimized build without any warnings. `cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug` not optimized build with debug information. Enable all debug Warnings. `cmake` minimal configuration, no optimization, minimal debug information --- This change isâ€‚[](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/562)

comment_regular_data.body:
[![CLA assistant check](https://cla-assistant.io/pull/badge/signed)](https://cla-assistant.io/TokTok/c-toxcore?pullRequest=562)
All committers have signed the CLA.
I'm a bit confused by this PR. Is it ready for review?

First of all, thank you for the contribution, but I doubt this will get merged. It adds a lot of complexity for, from what I can tell, no benefit.

What's better about this way of doing it?

Here are about 20 commits. We usually have 1 commit per PR. It looks like there are a few separate things here, e.g. documentation. Perhaps it makes sense to split it to make it easier to merge pieces rather than the whole thing.

Separately, please ensure that the indentation of cmake files is correct: 2-space indent per level.

Review status: 0 of 3 files reviewed at latest revision, 2 unresolved discussions, some commit checks failed.

---

*[CMakeLists.txt, line 81 at r3](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/562#-L4RCviwYjzCsAv_93BB:-L4RCviwYjzCsAv_93BC:b-t0v4bh) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/da724c8347718f012597b72dba16fb79bde3e047/CMakeLists.txt#L81)):*
> ```CMake
>   elseif(${CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE} STREQUAL "Debug")
>     set(CMAKE_C_FLAGS_DEBUG "-g3")
>     set(CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_DEBUG "-g3")
> ```

Also add `-gdwarf-2` for MINGW.

---

*[CMakeLists.txt, line 103 at r3](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/562#-L4RDBVKTTk8FRGdSnTx:-L4RDBVKTTk8FRGdSnTy:b-dp8j65) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/da724c8347718f012597b72dba16fb79bde3e047/CMakeLists.txt#L103)):*
> ```CMake
>   
>   # Disable all warnings for release
>   add_release_flag("-w")
> ```

Why completely remove all warnings in release mode?

---


*Comments from [Reviewable](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/562)*
<!-- Sent from Reviewable.io -->
@WarningX can you squash all your commits into one?
@WarningX also, I think travis builds a minimal build now. Is that intentional?
I think the default should be debug. Why is there a minimal configuration?

@WarningX I've fixed the things I noted, but this PR is broken. It sometimes completely forgets all flags, maybe it forgets the build type, I don't know. It happens when you run "make" after making a change to the CMakeLists.txt file. I'm done with this PR for now. I'll keep merging master into it on a best-effort basis, but if I end up changing the build too much so this PR no longer works, I'll close it. I generally like it, but it doesn't work reliably at the moment. Let me know when you have time to help fix it.

You can already use `CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release` or `CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug` though, [it's cmake's built-in](https://cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.10/variable/CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE.html), it will auto-magically add debug or release flags for everything you build when you specify one of those. I'm confused as to what this PR add on top of that?
Closing conflicting and unmaintained PR. Please reopen if you'd like to discuss it again.

commit.message:
Create new functions for debug and release flags

The necessary functions and macros are moved to AddFlags.cmake.
The new functions are backward compatible and add some new
functions to decide between debug, release and default compiler flags.
This makes building with CMake easier.

Use
"cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug .." for debug build
or
"cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release .." for release build
or
"cmake .."	for default build
